<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>
	<!--HOW TO CREATE DIALOGS USING RULESTRINGS
  
  - Activate "Log Grammar Resolution" on the Development Mode View Settings (3rd icon at the top) and grab the log entry when a pawn says something to see a list of all possible parameters for that type of interaction (with this mod, both "Constants" and "Custom Rules" are available).
  
  - For a pawn talk, each <li> is a possible thing to say. It might be assembled with parameters from that list or replaced with wildcards loaded from a subsequent <li>. Like this:
  
    <li>somewildcard(constraint1,constraint2)->Something to say [PARAMETER] about [wildcard]</li>
    <li>wildcard(constraint3)->subject to say case constraint3 is true.</li>
    <li>wildcard->subject to say without any constraints. </li>
    
  - The text is case-sensitive: wildcards must be all in lowercase.
    
  - For pawn talk, always start with "r_logentry->something"
  
  - Constraints are optional commands that regulate if that line is used or not. They can be:
    (p=x): Determines the probability the line is shown, with x being a whole number. 0 means no-show, 10 is a very high probability.
    (tag=x): Estabilishes a criteria to be used selecting lines down the line, with x being any word. If the tag matches the defName for another InteractionDef, that will be used to make a reply. 
    (requiredTag=x): Restricts the line to be used only when invoked by another line with that tag within the same InteractionDef.
    (debug): Triggers an error with the resolution trace on the Debug log. Good for debugging.
    (parameter==x): Restricts that line to be used only if the parameter satisfies the condition, with x being the required value.
    
  - The operators used on a comparsion might be "==" (equal to), "!=" (different from), ">" (greater than), "<" (lower than), ">=" (greater or equal) or "<="(lower of equal). EXCEPT the "<" character must be replaced by "&lt;" so the XML reader doesn't freak out. 
    
  - Without a constraint to say otherwise, the line will be selected randomly. Therefore, unless you're going for variety, add constraints to your lines. Example:
  
    <li>r_logentry(WEATHER==rain)->[rainTalk]</li>
    <li>raintalk(INITIATOR_trait==Pluviophile)->I love this rain!</li>
    <li>raintalk(INITIATOR_trait!=Pluviophile)->Damn this rain!</li>
    
    END OF INSTRUCTIONS-->
	<InteractionDef Name="SpeakUpReply" Abstract="True">
		<symbol>Things/Mote/SpeechSymbols/Speech</symbol>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>Salute</defName>
		<label>reply to salute</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.7)->Good [DAYPERIOD] to you too, [RECIPIENT_nameDef]! [ask]</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.5,INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.7)->Good [DAYPERIOD]. [ask]</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.3,INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.5)->Hmpf!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.3)->There's nothing good about it!</li>
				<li>ask(tag=WeatherAnswer)->Isn't it a lovely [DAYPERIOD]?</li>
				<li>ask(tag=HowAreYou)->How are you?</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>HowAreYou</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.7,INITIATOR_opinion>=5,tag=HowAreYou2)->I'm feeling great! What about you?</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.5,INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.7,INITIATOR_opinion>=5,tag=HowAreYou2)->I'm fine. What about you?</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.3,INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.5)->Could be better!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.3)->I hate my life!</li>
				<li>r_logentry->[INITIATOR_thoughtText]</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>HowAreYou2</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.7,INITIATOR_opinion>=-15)->I'm feeling great!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.5,INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.7,INITIATOR_opinion>=-15)->I'm fine.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood>=0.3,INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.5,INITIATOR_opinion>=-15)->Could be better!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_mood&lt;0.3,INITIATOR_opinion>=-15)->I hate my life!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_opinion>=-15)->[INITIATOR_thoughtText]</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>HuntWithFog</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry->You're right [RECIPIENT_nameDef], no hunting for me today. Too bad.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_shooting_level>=5,INITIATOR_animals_level>=5)->[RECIPIENT_nameDef], a skilled hunter like me doesn't need to wait for the perfect weather to hunt.</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>ReactToThought</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry->Eh, [RECIPIENT_nameDef] - you're right.</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>ReactToThought_NeedBeauty</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry->You're right, this place stinks!</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>WeatherClear</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry->Yes [RECIPIENT_nameDef], a clear sky is always an inspiring sight.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_opinion>=15)->You're right, [RECIPIENT_nameDef].</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_opinion&lt;=0)->At least on this I must agree with you, [RECIPIENT_nameDef].</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>WeatherFogOutdoors</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry(DAYPERIOD==morning)->At least we have some sunlight to help us see through.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(DAYPERIOD==morning)->With some luck, daylight should soon get rid of this fog.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(DAYPERIOD==afternoon)->Let's hope this fog ends before evening - it's really getting difficult to see things.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(DAYPERIOD==evening)->I can't see much either, I'm afraid.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(DAYPERIOD==night)->Foggy nights are perfect for trouble - maybe we should get back inside?</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_trait==pyromaniac)->I heard that bonfires help to dissipate fog.</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>WeatherFogToosmart</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_trait==too smart)->Correct, yet I do believe you wouldn't be able to determine its type. Well, I can: it's a [fog_type] fog.</li>
				<li>fog_type(DAYPERIOD==evening)->radiation</li>
				<li>fog_type(DAYPERIOD==night)->ground</li>
				<li>fog_type->freezing</li>
				<li>fog_type->frontal</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_intellectual_level>=10)->That is indeed the correct definition of fog.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_intellectual_level>=5,INITIATOR_intellectual_level&lt;10)->Mmm... yes, you are correct.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_intellectual_level&lt;5)->Err... what was that again?</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_intellectual_level&lt;5)->Wait - fog is... what!?</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_intellectual_passion==Minor)->That's quite interesting.</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_intellectual_passion==Major)->Fascinating!</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>
	<InteractionDef ParentName="SpeakUpReply">
		<defName>WeatherFogWimp</defName>
		<label>ensue</label>
		<logRulesInitiator>
			<rulesStrings>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_trait==brawler,INITIATOR_opinion&lt;10)->Come on, [RECIPIENT_nameDef] - stop being such a sissy! It's just fog!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_trait==brawler,INITIATOR_opinion>=15)->Don't worry, [RECIPIENT_nameDef] - if that happens, I'll just smash it out of existence!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_trait==wimp)->You're right, [RECIPIENT_nameDef] - this fog scares the hell out of me too!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_trait==wimp,INITIATOR_opinion>=15)->In that case, my dear [RECIPIENT_nameDef], we'll just make a run for it!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_opinion&lt;10)->[RECIPIENT_nameDef], don't be such a crybaby! It's fog - just fog!</li>
				<li>r_logentry(INITIATOR_opinion>=15)->No need to be afraid, [RECIPIENT_nameDef]. It's just normal fog.</li>
				<li>r_logentry->This fog could actually hide some danger, [RECIPIENT_nameDef] - especially at night...</li>
			</rulesStrings>
		</logRulesInitiator>
	</InteractionDef>

	
